INTRODUCTION

Digital literacy is an essential skill in today’s technology-driven world. It involves the ability to use digital tools effectively, communicate responsibly online, and stay safe from cyber threats. As part of the CSE0001 course, this project was designed to develop practical digital skills through hands-on activities. The project includes creating an infographic, building a professional digital portfolio, exploring coding and collaboration platforms, understanding email etiquette, and studying cybercrime awareness. These tasks helped in gaining a comprehensive understanding of responsible digital behavior.

------------------------------------------------------------

TASK 1 – DIGITAL LITERACY INFOGRAPHIC

In this task, I created a digital literacy awareness infographic using Canva. The infographic highlights key topics such as safe internet practices, useful digital tools for students, and maintaining a professional online presence. I used a clean layout with icons and minimal text to make the design visually appealing and easy to understand. One of the main challenges I faced was organizing information in a limited space without overcrowding the design. This task improved my ability to present information concisely and creatively.

------------------------------------------------------------

TASK 2 – DIGITAL PORTFOLIO

For this task, I created and updated profiles on GitHub, LinkedIn, and Kaggle. GitHub is used to store and manage coding projects, LinkedIn helps in building a professional network, and Kaggle provides a platform for learning data science and practicing problem-solving. Creating these profiles helped me understand the importance of maintaining a professional digital presence. In the future, I plan to regularly update my GitHub with projects, connect with professionals on LinkedIn, and improve my skills using Kaggle.

------------------------------------------------------------

TASK 3 – CODING & COLLABORATION PLATFORMS

In this task, I explored coding and collaboration platforms. I completed a beginner-level coding challenge on HackerRank, which helped me understand basic programming concepts and logic building. Additionally, I created a Google Form consisting of five questions related to digital literacy. This form can be used as a quiz to test awareness among students. These tools are useful for improving coding skills and collaborating effectively in academic work.

------------------------------------------------------------

TASK 4 – EMAIL ETIQUETTE

Professional communication is a key aspect of digital literacy. In this task, I drafted two professional emails—one requesting an assignment extension and another expressing interest in an internship. I ensured that both emails followed proper structure, including subject line, greeting, body, and sign-off. I also created a checklist of social media do’s and don’ts. This task helped me understand how poor communication can lead to misunderstandings and the importance of maintaining a professional tone in digital interactions.

------------------------------------------------------------

TASK 5 – CYBERCRIME AWARENESS

In this task, I studied phishing as a common cybercrime. Phishing involves attackers pretending to be trusted organizations to steal sensitive information such as passwords or bank details. I learned how these attacks occur through fake emails or links and how users can be easily tricked. I also created a prevention checklist with safety measures like verifying links, avoiding suspicious messages, and using two-factor authentication. This task increased my awareness of online threats and how to stay safe.

------------------------------------------------------------

CONCLUSION

This project helped me develop essential digital literacy skills required in academic and professional life. I learned how to use digital tools effectively, communicate professionally, and protect myself from cyber threats. These skills will be beneficial for my future studies and career.
